00:00:51.629 --> 00:00:58.479
sections seven inches long

00:01:11.280 --> 00:01:15.370
So update guys all of our eight pieces
are now cut and all of them are exactly

00:01:15.370 --> 00:01:19.330
the same length. In fact just to be sure
after they were cut I lined all them up

00:01:19.330 --> 00:01:22.630
together and sliced one more time down
the edge just to make sure they lined up

00:01:22.630 --> 00:01:26.080
perfectly smooth. Now since we were
chopping up wood anyway and we had some

00:01:26.080 --> 00:01:30.280
leftover I cut these two pieces five
inches long and another piece 20 inches

00:01:30.280 --> 00:01:33.370
long and you'll see what all these are
for in just a minute. So here's the basic idea.

00:01:33.370 --> 00:01:36.280
We're gonna take these four pieces
of wood and set them down on the table

00:01:36.280 --> 00:01:40.180
so two pieces are parallel to each other
and we'll use the other two pieces to

00:01:40.180 --> 00:01:43.180
cap them from the top of the bottom now
because we're going to be ramming sand

00:01:43.180 --> 00:01:46.509
into our system we want to screw these
together. But just for convenience I'm

00:01:46.509 --> 00:01:48.820
gonna be using my brad nailer to tack
them together and hold them in place

00:01:48.820 --> 00:02:03.030
until we can drill some pilot holes and
set the screws.

00:02:20.530 --> 00:02:24.050
So here we are guys I went ahead and
drilled pilot holes in each of the four

00:02:24.050 --> 00:02:27.830
corners and added a screw to bind them
down tightly and now we have two nearly

00:02:27.830 --> 00:02:31.280
identical wooden frames that fit
together just about perfectly. Now the

00:02:31.280 --> 00:02:33.680
purpose of the screws in the corners
here is to bind the wooden pieces

00:02:33.680 --> 00:02:36.860
together tight because once we start
ramming sand down in there it's going to

00:02:36.860 --> 00:02:40.160
apply a lot of pressure to the inside
walls if it's just nails holding that in

00:02:40.160 --> 00:02:43.040
there it's going to fall apart.
All right cool. So we got our two little

00:02:43.040 --> 00:02:46.100
box frames finished let's go ahead and
bring back these 5-inch pieces now and

00:02:46.100 --> 00:02:49.860
use them to create some latches.

00:03:06.459 --> 00:03:09.849
