blocks you can see I've just cut little

00:03:09.849 --> 00:03:12.489
triangles out of them and I did that by
stacking them together so they're

00:03:12.489 --> 00:03:16.180
perfectly symmetrical, and using the edge
of another piece of board as a guide to

00:03:16.180 --> 00:03:19.870
draw a triangle. Both of these pieces
went into the jaws of my bench vise to

00:03:19.870 --> 00:03:23.139
be held securely in place where I could
then use a jig saw to trace out the

00:03:23.139 --> 00:03:26.530
pattern. So now we have two little wooden
puzzle pieces whose triangles fit

00:03:26.530 --> 00:03:29.840
perfectly inside.
Let's go attach them to the box.

00:03:29.880 --> 00:03:33.360
We're going to need these wooden frames stacked
together as perfectly as possible, so for

00:03:33.370 --> 00:03:36.219
convenience I'm gonna be using clamps.
They're not necessary but it is going to

00:03:36.219 --> 00:03:39.430
make a job a lot easier.
take your block of wood and flip it

00:03:39.430 --> 00:03:43.359
around so your triangle is pointing
upward and separate the two pieces and

00:03:43.359 --> 00:03:46.599
place them on the side of your box. We want to place this on the side of our

00:03:46.599 --> 00:03:50.169
box with a triangle on the bottom piece
facing upward it's very important that

00:03:50.169 --> 00:03:53.709
the tip of it is below the centre line.
When the spacing looks good you can take

00:03:53.709 --> 00:03:57.879
the second piece and lock it into place
on top of the triangle. Center everything

00:03:57.879 --> 00:04:04.539
up so that it looks good, and then go
ahead and screw it into place.

00:04:28.350 --> 00:04:32.050
So check it out guys, our little metal
casting sandbox is just about finished.

00:04:32.050 --> 00:04:35.680
You can see I used two screws to screw
the triangle into place and then two

00:04:35.680 --> 00:04:39.190
screws on the top support as well as to
temporary screws on the bottom support.

00:04:39.190 --> 00:04:43.270
Those are designed to come out and when
they do, the two halves will separate.

00:04:43.270 --> 00:04:46.270
And for convenience you can see I've added a
few extra markings because once the two

00:04:46.270 --> 00:04:49.780
sides separate it's important to know
which way they go back together. On the

00:04:49.780 --> 00:04:53.169
two ends I drew two lines and added some
arrowheads so we know exactly where

00:04:53.169 --> 00:04:56.560
these are supposed to line up, and on the
front side I put an F on the triangle as

00:04:56.560 --> 00:05:00.910
well as the top piece, and the back side
got the letter B. See now the system is

00:05:00.910 --> 00:05:04.460
foolproof because if you try and put it
together backwards it won't fit and it

00:05:04.480 --> 00:05:08.920
will tell you why flip it around and it
goes together like a glove.

00:05:08.920 --> 00:05:12.960
